'''陳恩德'''， 是首位獲得三個[[米其林指南|米其林指南]]的香港廚師，從青少年早期就開始到餐廳工作，他退休之後而[[龍景軒|龍景軒]]餐廳擔任主廚。

== 生平 ==
年幼時母親過世，當時13至14歲的他開始在大三元餐廳工作<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/03/world/asia/03chef.html|title=A Chinese Chef’s Long Path to 3 Stars|last=Lau|first=Joyce Hor-Chung|date=2 January 2009|work=New York Times|accessdate=3 January 2009}}</ref><ref name="50best">{{Cite web|url=http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|title=Lung King Heen|accessdate=29 August 2012|work=The Worlds 50 Best Restaurants|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120828190245/http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|archivedate=2012-08-28}}</ref>。

由於他當時太年輕，不允許使用刀，在廚房的任務被限制在拔雞跟洗菜<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/03/world/asia/03chef.html|title=A Chinese Chef’s Long Path to 3 Stars|last=Lau|first=Joyce Hor-Chung|date=2 January 2009|work=New York Times|accessdate=3 January 2009}}</ref> 。在香港1970年代，他成為一位廚師，在多家餐廳服務過<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/03/world/asia/03chef.html|title=A Chinese Chef’s Long Path to 3 Stars|last=Lau|first=Joyce Hor-Chung|date=2 January 2009|work=New York Times|accessdate=3 January 2009}}</ref> ，包括[[福臨門|福臨門]]<ref name="50best">{{Cite web|url=http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|title=Lung King Heen|accessdate=29 August 2012|work=The Worlds 50 Best Restaurants|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120828190245/http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|archivedate=2012-08-28}}</ref>。1984年，他加入了一家[[香港洲際酒店|香港洲際酒店]]餐廳，之後成為行政主廚，在那裡工作了15年<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/03/world/asia/03chef.html|title=A Chinese Chef’s Long Path to 3 Stars|last=Lau|first=Joyce Hor-Chung|date=2 January 2009|work=New York Times|accessdate=3 January 2009}}</ref><ref name="50best">{{Cite web|url=http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|title=Lung King Heen|accessdate=29 August 2012|work=The Worlds 50 Best Restaurants|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120828190245/http://www.theworlds50best.com/regional-spotlights/hong-kong/lung-king-heen/|archivedate=2012-08-28}}</ref>。

